Install & configure DHCP server

1. Installing DHCP Server
sudo apt install isc-dhcp-server

2. Get you ip, subnet mask, broadcast by typing:
    
    ifconfig
    
    (Take note the the relelvant details from the appropriate interface, here, eth0)
    
3. Configure /etc/dhcp/dhcpd.conf (paste the three noted detaile from the above below)
  
  default-lease-time 600;
  max-lease-time 7200;

  subnet ip netmask broadcast {
   range 192.168.1.150 192.168.1.200;
   option routers 192.168.1.254;
  }
  
4. Edit /etc/default/isc-dhcp-server:
    INTERFACESv4: "eth0"
    
5. Type the commands as follows:
    - sudo systemctl enable isc-dhcp-server.service
    - sudo systemctl restart isc-dhcp-server.service
    - sudo systemctl status isc-dhcp-server.service
